<div data-post-info="">
      <p><span>Published:</span>
        <time datetime="2026-03-02T07:06:13">March 02, 2026, 7:06 pm</time>
      </p>
    </div>
    <article>
      <p>Welcome to Recap, our weekly feature--running every Monday morning--where we round up what’s been going on around video games, the internet and beyond.</p><hr><p>Marathon had a little open beta/playtest last week, which quite a few of us checked out. Bungie called it a 'Server Slam', and it ran across Steam, PS5 and Xbox Series X/S.</p><figure><a href="https://www.pcgamer.com/games/fps/marathon-server-slam-times-rewards/?ref=aftermath.site"><div><p>Here’s when you can play Marathon’s Server Slam and what exclusive rewards are up for grabs</p><p>Your go-to guide to the Marathon open preview weekend.</p><p><span>Rory Norris</span></p></div></a></figure><hr><p>Veteran developer Clint Hocking, who was working as director on the upcoming <em>Assassin's Creed: Hexe</em> project, has left not just the game but Ubisoft as well.</p><figure><a href="https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/assassins-creed-hexe-director-clint-hocking-has-left-ubisoft-as-part-of-franchise-upheaval/?ref=aftermath.site"><div><p>Assassin’s Creed: Hexe director, Clint Hocking, has left Ubisoft as part of franchise upheaval | VGC</p><p>Hocking previously helmed Splinter Cell: Chaos Theory, Far Cry 2, and Watch Dogs: Legion…</p><p><span>Video Games Chronicle</span><span>Andy Robinson</span></p></div></a></figure><hr><p>Full Circle, developers of the latest Skate game, have ben hit by layoffs; it's not known how many of the roughly 200-strong team were affected.</p><figure><a href="https://www.ea.com/ea-studios/full-circle/news/an-update-from-fullcircle?utm_campaign=skt_hd_ww_ic_ic_twt_fc-update-from-full-circle&amp;utm_source=twitter&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;cid=88627&amp;ts=1772049883093"><div><p>skate.’s Next Chapter - An Update from Full Circle</p><p>skate.’s Next Chapter - An Update from Full Circle</p><p><span>Electronic Arts Inc.</span><span>Electronic Arts</span></p></div></a></figure><hr><p>The organizers of British games conference Reboot Develop, Digitalna Avantura, have been "hit with a bankruptcy order over roughly €520,000 in unpaid debts".</p><figure><a href="https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/reboot-develop-organiser-issued-bankruptcy-order?ref=aftermath.site"><div><p>Reboot Develop organiser issued bankruptcy order</p><p>The company behind the boutique industry conference is reportedly 520,000 euro in debt.</p><p><span>Game Developer</span><span>Chris Kerr</span></p></div></a></figure><hr><p>I thought I'd seen every <em>Roblox </em>headline I could ever dream to see, and then along comes this:</p><figure><a href="https://www.404media.co/the-islamic-state-is-using-ai-to-resurrect-dead-leaders-and-platforms-are-failing-to-moderate-it/?ref=aftermath.site"><div><p>The Islamic State Is Using AI to Resurrect Dead Leaders and Platforms Are Failing to Moderate It</p><p>The group is talking about Epstein and filming propaganda videos in Roblox as a form of ‘digital Jihad,’ researchers say.</p><p><span>404 Media</span><span>Matthew Gault</span></p></div></a></figure><hr><p>Nacon, the publisher behind games like Hell is Us, RoboCop, and Test Drive Unlimited, has filed for insolvency.</p><figure><a href="https://gameinformer.com/2026/02/25/greedfall-2-publisher-nacon-files-for-insolvency-weeks-before-the-rpg-sequels-launch?ref=aftermath.site"><div><p>GreedFall 2 Publisher Nacon Files For Insolvency Weeks Before The RPG Sequel’s Launch</p><p>GreedFall launches March 12, but today, its publisher filed for insolvency.</p><p><span>Game Informer</span><span>Wesley LeBlanc</span></p></div></a></figure>
    </article>

        

      

          

  
  
  
